{
  "stem": "26142.18",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was very cold, and, and, and people that either they had fever or whatever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we stopped at one, at one station, the, the, the German SS ordered the Ukrainian SS-- they had the dark uniforms, and the other had the green uniforms-- they ordered them to take the dead people out, because they didn't want the local people to see or something.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When they started taking the dead people out from, from our, our wagon, we asked them to leave the, to leave the blankets.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They did leave the blankets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So by the second, the third day, we had, each one had plenty of blankets.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were able to, to cover ourselves and protect ourselves from the, from the freezing cold.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the third or fourth day, we arrived in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't know it was Dachau.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when haftlings that were send out from the camp to help us unload the dead and the living, we asked them, where are we, so that then we found out that we are in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember they were taking off, they were taking off the, the dead and putting on, on, on, on one cart and then taking off the living.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were carrying inside and put them on the ground there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had to-- you know, the Germans are very meticulous.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they had to account for how many dead and how many alive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it, if it would matter to-- anyway.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Anyway, I remember the two guys spoke in Polish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one said to the other in Polish, he says, [SPEAKING POLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They put them on, on the dead cart.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the one said to him, he is still alive.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
